TITLE: The 2022 Oscars updates
SUMMARY: Amy Schumer, Wanda Sykes and Regina Hall are hosting the 94th annual Academy Awards. Follow here for live updates from the red carpet and the latest on the winners.

TITLE: El Salvador proclaims state of emergency as homicides soar
SUMMARY: El Salvador's legislative assembly approved a state of emergency law early Sunday to tackle a spiraling homicide rate -- driven by gangs Barrio 18 and MS-13 -- after the country's police forces reported 62 homicides on Saturday.

TITLE: The number that puts Vladimir Putin at risk
SUMMARY: The official Soviet death toll during the Afghan War, which lasted more than nine years, was around 15,000 soldiers. It is therefore quite telling that the Russians may have already lost as many 15,000 soldiers in just one month in Ukraine, according to estimates given to CNN by senior NATO officials.

TITLE: These Russian journalists found a way to report from outside the country
SUMMARY: Russia's independent news network, TV Rain, shuttered its Moscow operations in early March â€” its newsroom empty, broadcast signal shut off.

TITLE: Max Verstappen claims first win of F1 season after enthralling battle with Charles LeClerc at Saudi Arabian Grand Prix
SUMMARY: Reigning world champion Max Verstappen won the Saudi Arabian Grand Prix on Sunday after a thrilling battle with Charles LeClerc.

TITLE: How to help the people of Ukraine
SUMMARY: Russian bombardments and fighting continue throughout Ukraine sending people fleeing for safety.

TITLE: Putting your Covid diagnosis on blast is no longer a thing
SUMMARY: Governments and health officials acknowledge that the Covid-19 virus may be around in some form for a very long time. That means learning to coexist with it -- without resorting to screaming headlines for every new case contracted by a celebrity, says Peggy Drexler.

TITLE: Colorado firefighters make gains against a Boulder-area wildfire that forced thousands to evacuate
SUMMARY: Just one day after a wildfire spurred evacuation orders for 19,000 people in Colorado, the inferno is already 21% contained, officials said Sunday.

TITLE: Country music singer and police officer Jeff Carson dies at 58
SUMMARY: Award-winning country music singer Jeff Carson has died at the age of 58, according to a statement from the singer's publicist.

TITLE: Blinken: 'Deal or no deal' US will work to deter Iran nuclear capability
SUMMARY: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken committed Sunday to countering hostile actions from Iran regardless of whether the US can reestablish a nuclear agreement with the country, hours after the US special envoy to Iran stressed that a deal "is not inevitable."

TITLE: Elon Musk says he's seriously considering creating a new social media platform
SUMMARY: Elon Musk said he is giving "serious thought" to creating a new social media platform in a tweet Saturday.

TITLE: Biden's off-the-cuff remark on Putin sends shock waves on dramatic final day of trip
SUMMARY: At nearly the same moment President Joe Biden declared him a "butcher," Vladimir Putin's missiles began falling in Lviv, Ukraine.

TITLE: Ukrainians disrupt and derail Russian offensive as war moves to new phase
SUMMARY: Just over a month after the first ballistic missiles slammed into Kyiv's international airport, the Russian campaign has been disrupted and derailed by stubborn Ukrainian resistance -- and in the last few days by agile Ukrainian counterattacks on several fronts.

TITLE: Shanghai to lock down each half of city for mass Covid-19 testing
SUMMARY: Shanghai will be locking down each half of the city by turns for mass Covid-19 testing starting Monday amid surging infections across the city, according to the statement published by the Shanghai government Sunday night.

TITLE: Cory Booker reflects on Ketanji Brown Jackson hearings: 'This is not about racism. It's about decency'
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Cory Booker of New Jersey said Sunday that there were moments during Supreme Court nominee Ketanji Brown Jackson's confirmation hearings last week that invoked a "familiar hurt" many Americans could relate to.

TITLE: This movie offends precisely nobody
SUMMARY: Tracking this year's Oscar prospects reminds us that nothing -- not our movies, how we watch them, what they mean to us, or the Academy Awards that burnish them -- will ever be the same, writes Gene Seymour.

TITLE: Here's how to make the Oscars more watchable
SUMMARY: The Academy Awards ceremony is Hollywood's biggest night, and for decades, it was one of the most watched television events each year.

TITLE: Prince William says he respects any country's decision to become a republic
SUMMARY: Britain's Prince William says he's not in the business of "telling people what to do" and any future relationship between countries in the Caribbean and the UK is "for the people to decide."

TITLE: Wildlife officials catch 500-pound bear roaming near a Tennessee university
SUMMARY: A 500-pound black bear prowling around a Tennessee university has been captured and relocated, according to the Tennessee Wildlife Resources Agency.

TITLE: A fire at an Exxon refinery draws firefighters from multiple departments
SUMMARY: A structure fire at an ExxonMobil refinery in Montana burned for more than three hours, officials said Sunday.

TITLE: Boeing's problems in China go far beyond the latest grounding
SUMMARY: Another Boeing plane has been grounded after a fatal crash, this time in China. That may be the least of the company's problems in a crucial market.

TITLE: Why Biden hasn't scored a political win from canceling $17 billion in student loans
SUMMARY: Joe Biden has canceled more student loan debt than any other President, delivering relief to 700,000-plus borrowers. But some voters feel misled by Biden, who had supported canceling $10,000 for each of the 43 million federal student loan borrowers while on the campaign trail.

TITLE: Russia invades Ukraine
SUMMARY: The western Ukrainian city of Lviv was hit by strikes from Russia's military, officials said, as US President Joe Biden urged unity in Poland. Follow here for live news updates.

TITLE: NYC aims to reduce racial inequities in maternal health care by offering free access to doulas
SUMMARY: New York City is to offer free access to doulas for families in the city's most vulnerable neighborhoods.

TITLE: Oscars stars used to play pretend during times of war. Not anymore
SUMMARY: The world is facing down a threat to smother an independent nation, as well as the whole notion of free expression. If you're in the business of creating art of any kind, you have to be willing to stand up for that right.

TITLE: Four people are dead after a driver crashed a vehicle into Salem, Oregon, encampment of unhoused people
SUMMARY: Four people died early Sunday morning after a motorist crashed a vehicle into an encampment of unhoused people in Salem, Oregon, according to a news release from the Salem Police Department.

TITLE: You asked, we answered: How to help Ukrainian refugees
SUMMARY: Google searches asking how to help Ukrainian refugees have been spiking in the United States. Here's what we know so far about the answers.

TITLE: The texts that shook the Supreme Court
SUMMARY: "Presidents come and go," said William Howard Taft, "but the Supreme Court goes on forever." Two stories relating to the Supreme Court's awesome power dominated US politics last week -- the confirmation hearing for Ketanji Brown Jackson and the revelation of texts disputing the 2020 election result from Ginni Thomas

TITLE: Atari's 'Home Pong' prototype sells at auction for more than $270K
SUMMARY: If you think the PS5 is expensive, get a load of Atari's "Home Pong" prototype.

TITLE: Rep. Mo Brooks says Trump repeatedly asks him to 'rescind' the 2020 election
SUMMARY: Rep. Mo Brooks of Alabama repeated his claim Thursday that former President Donald Trump has personally asked him to work to rescind the 2020 election, remove Joe Biden from office and install Trump in his place.
